en_144287_0	A Shortage of cigarettes has occurred in the market after the cabinet decision to increase the price of cigarettes was announced.
en_144287_1	The cabinet decided to impose 15 percent VAT on cigarettes, and increase the production tax by 5 rupees for all cigarettes despite its quantity or brand.
en_144287_2	However, the ADIC noted that the relevant gazette notification has not been released so far.
en_144287_3	It has been reported to our news team that cigarettes are being sold at various prices by certain vendors.
en_144287_4	However, in response to a question raised by the reporters following a ceremony held in Mutwal today, Finance Minister Ravi Karunanayake noted that stringent measures will be taken against the vendors who conceal stocks of cigarettes.
en_144287_5	The Minister also noted that measures would be taken to minimize smoking, eventually leading to its elimination.
